    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) is a superlative example of the marque's 'Gram Strategy' engineering. At its heart is a perfectly maintained 13B-REW twin-rotor engine featuring its factory-spec sequential twin-turbocharger system, providing seamless boost transition across the rev range. The chassis retains its original front-midship balance and lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension, ensuring surgical turn-in. Power is delivered through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential. This vehicle has been meticulously preserved, with no modifications to the vacuum line 'rat's nest' or thermal management systems, making it a rare, turn-key investment for the serious purist.",
      "price": 46500.0,
